    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NAS Key Set Identifier IE encoding/decoding format inconsistency\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_nas_key_set_identifier` function was not behaving as expected due to an inconsistency between its implementation format and usage context. The function was implemented using a \"Type & Value\" format where IEI and data were combined in a single byte, but it was being used in contexts that expected the standard TLV (Tag-Length-Value) format with separate IEI and data bytes.\n\nThis caused incorrect parsing of NAS messages containing the NAS Key Set Identifier information element, particularly in Tracking Area Update Request messages where the IEI value 0xB0 was not being properly handled.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/NasKeySetIdentifier.c`: \n  - Modified `decode_nas_key_set_identifier` to use proper TLV format with full byte IEI comparison and separate data byte reading\n  - Updated `encode_nas_key_set_identifier` to follow TLV format instead of \"Type & Value\" format\n  - Fixed `encode_u8_nas_key_set_identifier` to properly encode only the data byte without IEI handling\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/NasKeySetIdentifier.h`: No changes needed to header file\n\nWhen processing NAS messages with NAS Key Set Identifier IEs, the decoder now properly validates the full IEI byte (0xB0) before reading the associated data from the subsequent byte, resolving the unexpected behavior previously observed.\n"
}